metadata.name: String art generator #229
metadata.description:
Generative image with animation (1024x1024px) Vanilla JS

This project is a string-art simulator which weaves some patterns in different layouts to make beautiful compositions which can be played from the beginning.
The main features of this generative collection are the several Patterns and Layouts which combined make a huge amount of variations.

“Pattern” defined as the instructions that the thread has to follow to weave the result.
"Layout" defined as the setup of the nails on the board.

The thread is always continuous without interruptions.

Features:

Pattern (21)
Layout (10)
Palette (25)
Layout Mirror (None, Horizontal, Vertical)
ThreadType: (Silk, Wool)
ThreadThickness: (Regular, Thick)

Controls:

[P] Play. 
[R] Result.
[U] Undo. 
[N] Nails. Show/Hide the nails.

[S] Download snapshot (may be slow or unresponsive)

You can weave yourself
Click to change the thread color

This project is an homage to Mary Everest Boole who, more than 100 years ago, used string art to teach math to children.

metadata.name: Singularity #20
metadata.description:
How and why the universe was created?
The fundamental question of the world which concerns all people and also inspired me to create a simple model of the universe's most exciting object. Black holes have incredibly high gravity because of their heaviness and thickness, so even the light can not escape from it.

Features:
- Light Color (the rarest is the Bright Turquoise)
- Gravity
- Waves

Interaction:
If you click on the black hole, you can make alive the dead star again.

Bálint Kulcsár, 2021

metadata.name: Curvatur3 Mov3m3nts #23
metadata.description:
Curvature Movements first edition was issued one year ago !
Made with p5js.
August 2023

Keys:
Press 2 -> 4000 x 4000 png
Press 3 -> 6000 x 6000 png
Press 4 -> 8000 x 8000 png
Press 5 -> 10000 x 10000 png
Press s -> 10000 x 10000 png
Press 6 -> 12000 x 12000 png
Then press s to save png (default size is 2000x2000)

ABOUT THE CREATOR

Obsukiy is a french painter and digital artist based in Berlin.
https://twitter.com/ObsukiyArt

metadata.name: TRIP #121
metadata.description:
Generate your own acid TRIP ⦿◡⦿

FEATURES:
• 4 Diffirent sizes: 2x2, 3x3, 4x4, 5x5
• 25 Diffirent forms
• 10 Diffirent hieroglyphs (small % of spawn)
• Infinite amount of background color schemes
• 2 Types of background animations
• 9 Diffirent textures for background

INTERACTIVE:
• Hover cursor over hieroglyph to see translation title
• Hover cursor over any other element to highlight
• Click to PAUSE, second click to UNPAUSE

Have a great trip! ⦿◡⦿
Made by @likemurvin

metadata.name: Scratches #18
metadata.description:
The work is configured as a dynamic visual composition in which the geometric patterns move and overlap, creating an effect of scratches and visual intertwining. The colors vary in intensity over time, creating a feeling of constant change and movement. The work invites the viewer to immerse themselves in a suggestive and contemplative visual experience, in which the combination of patterns and colors generates a sensation of intriguing beauty and complexity.
The title evokes the idea of signs that leave traces and scratch the surface of perception. This suggestion recalls the work of Jacques Derrida, who investigated the concept of "difference" and underlined the importance of traces and marginalities in the act of signifying.
In summary, "Scratches" is a combination of generative aesthetics and philosophical references that invite viewers to reflect on the nature of appearance, trace and reality itself, opening new perspectives on the complexities of existence.
